webhooks.description:
Send this object as another transactional notification option. In case you have a **Webhook** created through the Console, the notification will be sent to both the **API** and the **Console** channels. It means they will not be mutually exclusive.

The notifications will be seen in the Webhooks Notifications dashboard, and they will have a new field called Configuration, which will identify the source of the notification.

**Example:**

```Example
{
  "webhooks": [
    {
      "events": [
        "approvedTransaction",
        "declinedTransaction"
      ],
      "headers": [
        {
          "label": "json",
          "value": "12"
        }
      ],
      "urls": [
        "https://eof2hhkrta4ooo1.m.pipedream.net"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

webhooksItem.description:
Send this array as another transactional notification option. Each element in the array is a webhook configuration object. In case you have a **Webhook** created through the Console, the notification will be sent to both the **API** and the **Console** channels. It means they will not be mutually exclusive.

The notifications will be seen in the Webhooks Notifications dashboard, and they will have a new field called Configuration, which will identify the source of the notification.

> #### Colombia 🇨🇴 — Bre-B: `keyResolution` in webhook payload
>
> The `webhooks` field is an **array**. Wrap your webhook configuration object in `[ ]`. Example: `"webhooks": [{ "events": [...], "urls": [...] }]`
>
> When a Transfer Out transaction belongs to a Colombian merchant with the Bre-B processor configured, the webhook payload includes the `keyResolution` object for both `approvedTransaction` and `declinedTransaction` events. `ownerName` is returned masked. `bankId`, `documentNumber`, and `documentType` are **not** included in the Bre-B webhook payload. Merchants from other countries or using a different processor receive the standard webhook payload without `keyResolution`.
>
> ```json
> {
>   "transactionStatus": "APPROVAL",
>   "ticketNumber": "1703256781234567",
>   "keyResolution": {
>     "keyValue": "3001234567",
>     "ownerName": "M**** G**** L****"
>   }
> }
> ```

**Example:**

```Example
{
  "webhooks": [
    {
      "events": [
        "approvedTransaction",
        "declinedTransaction"
      ],
      "headers": [
        {
          "label": "json",
          "value": "12"
        }
      ],
      "urls": [
        "https://eof2hhkrta4ooo1.m.pipedream.net"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

